@Article{	  c130,
  abstractnote	= {The NSF NCAR C-130 is a versatile and capable research
		  platform that carries a wide variety of scientific
		  payloads. The C-130 has a 10-hour flight endurance, a 2,900
		  nautical mile range at up to 27,000 ft, and a payload
		  capacity of up to 13,000 lbs. In addition to standard
		  thermodynamic, microphysics and radiation sensors, the
		  C-130 has a roomy fuselage payload area (414 ft2) and many
		  versatile inlets and optical ports. The aircraft carries
		  instruments and sensors in pods and pylons on both wings.
		  The C-130 can carry advanced EOL and community
		  instrumentation.},
